authors: Zhang, C., Ju, Y., Tang, N., Li, Y., Zhang, G., Song, Y., Fang, H., Yang, L., Feng, J., 2020
title: Systematic analysis of supervised machine learning as an effective approach to predicate β-lactam resistance phenotype in Streptococcus pneumoniae
contributions: I helped with rechecking the correctness of previously used protein data.

authors: Jiang, L., Zheng, Z., Fang, H., Yang, J., 2021
title: A generalized linear mixed model association tool for biobank-scale data
contributions: I implemented the ACAT module based on R scripts provided by Longda. I improved the efficiency of the module by optimizing the data structure and program design.

authors: Tang, N., Hu, J., Zhao, Y., Song, Y., Wang, C., Zhang, G., Wei, D., Fang, H., Li, C., Jia, R., Feng, J., 2022
title: In vivo evolution of carbapenem resistance in hypervirulent Klebsiella pneumoniae in a patient undergoing long-term treatment
contributions: I assisted with phylogenetic tree clustering in this project. When a phylogenetic tree contains thousands of nodes, manually analyzing such tree become difficult. To address this, I developed a tool that automatically clusters the tree. The code is stored in repository biotools.

authors: Qi, T., Wu, Y., Fang, H., Zhang, F., Liu, S., Zeng, J., Yang, J., 2022
title: Genetic control of RNA splicing and its distinct role in complex trait variation
contributions: I built the data portal called BrainMeta. The website is based on the open project Pheweb, and I ran the data parsing process of Pheweb and modified the webpage to meet our needs. I https://yanglab.westlake.edu.cn/software/osca/#THISTLEalso implemented the permutation module named THISTLE.

authors: Zhang, G., Yao, S., Liu, Y., Fang, H., Song, Y., Wang, C., Wei, D., Feng, J., 2023
title: Systematic discovery of a new catalogue of tyrosine-type integrases in bacterial genomic islands
contributions: Assist in identifying long repeats within bacterial genomes. I developed a program that can identify long repetitive sequences, even when their short segments contain variations. This program can now identify long repetitive sequences that follow a particular simple segment pattern.
